Applicable Standards and References (indicative)
  - eIDAS Regulation (EU) No 910/2014 (relevant Articles for Qualified services)
  - ETSI EN 319 401 (General Policy Requirements)
  - ETSI EN 319 411-1 and ETSI EN 319 411-2 (TSPs issuing certificates; qualified)
  - ETSI EN 319 412 series (Certificate Profiles; naming and identity attributes)
  - RFC 5280 (X.509), RFC 6960 (OCSP) – awareness level for RA-relevant touchpoints
  - ETSI TS 119 461 (Remote identity proofing) – if remote identification is used

Minimum Expected Contents (for the final PDF)
  1) Cover Page
     - Title: “RA Operator – Training & Certification Pack”
     - Organization: GreekTrustCo
     - Version/Issue Date
     - Approvals: RA Manager / QTS Manager signatures and dates

  2) Role and Authorization Framework
     - RA Operator role description, responsibilities, and authority limits
     - Segregation of duties (RA vs. PKI/CA, Security, Crypto Officers, QA/Audit)
     - Authorization roster:
       • Operator full name, unique ID/username
       • Authorization scope (QES/QSeal; natural vs. legal persons; in-person vs. remote)
       • Effective date, expiry/renewal date
       • Supervisor (RA Manager) and secondary approver (as applicable)

  3) Training Curriculum (syllabus)
     - eIDAS/ETSI overview: obligations for RA functions
     - Identity proofing (natural persons):
       • In-person checks; document authentication; photo match
       • Remote identification (if applicable): liveness, video session, integrity controls (per ETSI TS 119 461)
       • Handling of high-assurance eID means (if used)
     - Identity proofing (legal persons):
       • Organization identity, legal existence, authority to act
       • Verification of signatory’s mandate; evidence capture (GEMH/registry extracts)
     - Attribute accuracy for certificate profiles (ETSI EN 319 412):
       • Subject DN, SAN, QCStatements mapping; data minimization
     - Enrollment and evidence management:
       • Evidence capture, integrity, chain of custody, storage/retention
       • Privacy and GDPR basics for RA (lawful basis, minimization, redaction)
     - Revocation intake and processing:
       • Authentication of requester; urgent revocations; fraud/compromise cases
       • Escalation and after-hours procedures
     - Systems and security:
       • RA workstation hardening, MFA, session control, clean desk
       • Logging and audit trails; time synchronization awareness
     - Anti-fraud and red flags:
       • Suspicious patterns, document tampering indicators, social engineering
       • Reporting channels and incident escalation to Security/Compliance
     - Quality control:
       • Sampling, peer review/4-eyes (where applicable), error correction
     - Code of conduct and ethics:
       • Independence, conflicts, integrity; disciplinary measures

  4) Training Delivery and Evidence
     - Training plan and schedule (initial and refresher)
     - Attendance logs per session (date, duration, trainer, modality)
     - Training materials index (slides, manuals, SOP references)

  5) SOP and Policy Acknowledgements (signed by each RA Operator)
     - Acknowledgement statements and dates for:
       • TSPS sections governing RA processes
       • Identity proofing SOP (in-person and remote, if used)
       • Evidence capture and retention SOP
       • Revocation request handling SOP
       • Privacy/Data protection SOP
       • Information Security & Acceptable Use policies for RA
     - Version references and document IDs

  6) Assessments and Certifications
     - Written/online test results (score, pass/fail, date)
     - Practical evaluation checklists (supervised enrollments; scenario-based)
     - Issued training certificates (internal or external) with IDs and validity
     - Remediation/retraining records (if any)

  7) Authorization and Periodic Review
     - Authorization letters or forms countersigned by RA Manager/QTS Manager
     - Review cadence (e.g., annual), triggers for early review (policy changes, incidents)
     - Suspension/revocation of RA authorization process (if applicable)

  8) Privacy and Minimization
     - Personal data contained in this pack minimized and redacted where feasible
     - No inclusion of sensitive personal data beyond what is strictly necessary
     - Retention aligned with Recordkeeping Policy; secure storage and access control

  9) Exception Handling and Incidents
     - Process for documenting exceptions from standard RA procedures
     - Linkage to incident response (security/privacy incidents; suspected fraud)
     - Lessons learned and continuous improvement tracking

  10) Document Control
     - Version history, approvers, next review date
     - Distribution list and classification

